# Changelog

All notable changes to this project are documented here. The format is based on
[Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/), and this project
adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [Unreleased]

### Added

- Configurable alternate toolbar action for Command-click on macOS and
  Ctrl-click on Windows or Linux, defaulting to visible-region capture.

## [1.1.0] - 2026-06-08

### Added

- Toolbar icon action setting with four options:
  - Show the capture menu.
  - Capture the whole web page.
  - Capture the visible region.
  - Capture a web page region.
- Firefox shortcut commands for showing the capture menu and running each
  capture mode directly.
- Default shortcuts:
  - `Alt+Shift+S` shows the capture menu.
  - `Ctrl+Shift+S` captures the whole web page.
- "Manage Keyboard Shortcuts" button in settings, opening Firefox's built-in
  extension shortcut manager.
- "Play sounds" setting, enabled by default.

### Changed

- Reordered capture menu actions to whole page, visible region, then web page
  region.
- Raised the minimum supported Firefox version to 137.0 for built-in shortcut
  settings support.

## [1.0.0] - 2026-06-07

First release of the **Easy Screenshot Plus** fork, continuing maintenance of
the inactive upstream `mozilla-extensions/easyscreenshot`.

### Added

- Settings page (options UI) with two preferences:
  - One-click whole-page capture when the toolbar icon is clicked (skips the
    popup menu).
  - Toggle for opening the download folder after saving (off by default).
- "Settings" entry in the toolbar icon's right-click menu, opening the options
  page.
- `LICENSE` (MPL-2.0), `README.md`, and this changelog.

### Changed

- The system file manager (Finder/Explorer) no longer opens after saving a
  screenshot; it is now opt-in via the new setting.
- Saved files use macOS-style names, e.g.
  `Screenshot 2026-06-07 at 6.14.17 PM.png`.
- Options page now follows the browser's light/dark theme instead of a forced
  white background.
- Renamed the extension to "Easy Screenshot Plus" with a new add-on ID
  (`easy-screenshot-plus@quietmindcreative.com`).
- Modernized the lint toolchain to ESLint 9 (flat config) and added `web-ext`
  for current-Firefox validation.
- Modernized the manifest: `browser_specific_settings` (replacing the deprecated
  `applications` key) and an explicit `data_collection_permissions` of `none`.
